Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Now get the veggies prepped! Cut the core out of the @green pepper{1} and @yellow pepper{1} and cut them into slices about 2cm wide. Peel and chop the @red onion{1} into roughly 3cm pieces. Cut the @courgette{1} in half lengthways, then cut each half into four lengths. Next chop those lengths into batons roughly the length of your little finger.

Put the peppers and onion on a #baking tray{}. Mix together 2 tbsp of @oil{2%tbsp}, the @jerk sauce{1} and the @mango chutney{1} in a #bowl{} and drizzle this over the veggies. Add ¼ tsp of @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @pepper{} to the tray, give it a good shake until everything is well coated. Prick the @spicy sausages{4} with a sharp #knife{} (twice per sausage) and pop them on top of the veggies.

Pop your baking tray on the top shelf of your oven and roast for ~{25%minutes}. Halfway through cooking add the courgettes, give the baking tray a shake and put it back in your oven.

In the meantime, bring a large #pot{} of water to the boil with ¼ tsp of @salt{1/4%tsp}. Peel and chop the @potato{1} into roughly 2cm pieces and add them to your boiling water. Boil for ~{10%minutes} until soft.

> The potatoes are done when you can easily slip a knife through them.

While the potatoes are cooking roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{3}.

Once your potatoes are cooked, drain them, return to the pot and add 1 tbsp of @butter{1%tbsp}, 3 tbsp of @milk{3%tbsp}, ¼ tsp of @salt{1/4%tsp} and a grind of @pepper{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until you have a smooth consistency.

> If your potatoes are cooked before your sausages and veg, simply put a lid on your potato pot until everything else is ready, they will wait.

When your sausages are browned and your veggies are cooked, get your baking tray out of your oven and stir the parsley through your veggie mixture. Serve your mash with your sausages and veggies piled on top and enjoy!